2001_January 19 

The fifth element is a classic sci-fi/comedy destined to be a great cult
film years from it's 1997 debut.  After the first viewing you may find
yourself feeling a that you were entertained but may be slightly confused
due to the fast editing.  After two or three screenings you probably will
place this film on your favorites list.  The film is nearly flawless.  The
direction is extrememly detailed and nearly every frame has meaning and
purpose.   Hilarious comedy, excellent special effects, a unique sound
track, interesting characters, quality acting, and a fun story make this
film a must for your VCR or DVD library.  The details will make you want
to
see it several times.    
